 to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger FitzRichard , Lord of Warkworth was born in 1129, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Fitz Euchace, was 19 and his mother, Jane Bigod, was 36. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Adeliza de Vere. He died in 1190, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1129–1190":"1129–1190","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1150–1190":"1150–1190","1167–1214":"1167–1214","1110–1163":"1110–1163","1093–1129":"1093–1129","1190":"1190","1110":"1110","1163":"1163","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","1093":"1093","1129":"1129","after 1129":"pärast 1129","Abt 1150":"umbes 1150","1214":"1214","1125":"1125","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","after 1185":"pärast 1185","Warkworth, Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Warkworth, Northumberland, England","Raby, Durham, England":"Raby, Durham, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1129–1190":"1129–1190","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1150–1190":"1150–1190","1167–1214":"1167–1214","1110–1163":"1110–1163","1093–1129":"1093–1129","1190":"1190","1110":"1110","1163":"1163","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","1093":"1093","1129":"1129","after 1129":"1129 jälkeen","Abt 1150":"noin 1150","1214":"1214","1125":"1125","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","after 1185":"1185 jälkeen","Warkworth, Alnwick, 